The paper focuses on natural language understanding and specifically on natural language inference, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses unsupervised pretraining, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The addition of external knowledge to NLI models may involve techniques such as knowledge graphs or embeddings, which are also relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
